From Subject Re Looking for drawing packages In article greg greg Gregory Lehman writes Path gatech usc utnut torn nott geovision greg From greg Gregory Lehman Newsgroups Subject Looking for drawing packages Message ID greg Date Apr GMT Organization Kanata Ontario Lines Xref I am developing an application that allows a user to interactively create edit view a visual model topology of their network and I was wondering if anyone knew of any builder tools that exist to simplify this In the past I have used Visual Edge's UIM X product to develop other GUIs so I am familiar with UIMSs in The topology will support objects and connecting Once the topology is created I want to provide the user with capabilities to support grouping zooming I am looking for some form of a higher abstraction other than X drawing routines to accomplish Specifically the zooming and grouping aspects may prove difficult and certainly time consuming if I have to roll my own Suggestions greg You don't mention your platform but Digital has a custom widget NetEd which does exactly what you want to Cost is nominal or so call your local The widget is supported on a variety of platforms and I heard rumblings of porting to Sun so it may be worth the Charlie Gilley Digital Equipment